    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "From my experience, `map`, `foreach`, `filter` and `reduce` are very raw tools. If you want to do something that is not well suited with one of the first three, you end up using the fourth (reduce) which is quite hard to grasp if you're not used to it.\n\nLodash contains lots of shortcuts to avoid bloating your code. This makes the code very explicit as the function name is usually explicit about what you're trying to achieve, thus more readable.\n\nOne thing that could be very important for this issue, would be a static analysis of our usage of the lodash library. What I have in mind here, is to be able to figure what kind of usage we do lodash, `are we using basic functionnalities (map, reduce and co, or more fancy functions)?`, `where are we using those functions?`, `do we use shortcut syntax?`.\n",
